# Lootlyfe - Cursor Rules

## Architecture principles
- Feature-based folders in /src/features, never layer-based
- Each feature owns its api/, hooks/, components/, types.ts
- Shared UI lives in /src/shared/components
- No business logic in /app screens - screens call hooks from features

## Data layer
- All Supabase calls go through /src/features/{feature}/api/
- All server state is managed by TanStack Query - never useState for server data
- Client-only state uses Zustand stores in /src/stores
- Never call supabase.from() directly in a component

## Types
- Strict TypeScript everywhere
- Database types come from /src/shared/types/database.ts (generated)
- Never use `any`. Use `unknown` if truly unknown, then narrow.

## Forms
- Always use react-hook-form + zod resolver
- Validation schemas live next to the form component

## Styling
- Always use theme tokens from /src/shared/theme, never hard-code colors or spacing
- Respect dark mode via useTheme()
- All text must use the Text component from /src/shared/components

## Accessibility (non-negotiable)
- Every pressable must have accessibilityLabel and accessibilityRole
- Every screen must support Dynamic Type
- Test with VoiceOver before considering any screen done

## Analytics
- Every user-initiated action fires a PostHog event via /src/shared/lib/posthog.ts
- Event names follow snake_case and match the approved event list in /docs/analytics-events.md

## AI features
- AI suggestion calls go through /src/features/ai-suggestions only
- All AI features must be skippable - never block core flows
- Cache AI responses aggressively to control cost

## Security
- RLS policies enforce all permissions - never trust the client
- Kids cannot see other kids' data in the same family
- High-value rewards require parent approval (enforced server-side)

## Commits
- Use conventional commits: feat:, fix:, chore:, refactor:, docs:
- Reference the phase when scaffolding: "feat(phase-1): add theme tokens"
